          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2"><span class="font-mono text-blue-400 text-[10px]">L15</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-300">Homogeneity detection: if all channels equal, IC = F and C = 0</span></div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2"><span class="font-mono text-blue-400 text-[10px]">L18</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-300">Closure perturbation: small threshold change → bounded stance change</span></div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-kernel-600 mt-1">+ L11–L14, L16–L17 (Lipschitz constants, monotone maps, variance bounds)</div>
        </div>`
    },
    {
      range: 'L19–L25', name: 'Seam & Weld', count: 7, color: 'text-green-400', borderColor: 'border-green-700 hover:border-green-500',
      description: 'Residual sensitivity, composition law, and return stability. These prove that the seam budget is well-behaved and composable.',
      keyLemmas: `
        <div class="space-y-1.5">
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2"><span class="font-mono text-green-400 text-[10px]">L20</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-300">Seam composition law — multi-seam chains accumulate in O(1)</span></div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2"><span class="font-mono text-green-400 text-[10px]">L23</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-300">Kernel Lipschitz continuity on ε-clipped domain</span></div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-kernel-600 mt-1">+ L19, L21–L22, L24–L25 (residual bounds, weld pre/post tests, return topology)</div>
        </div>`
    },
    {
      range: 'L26–L34', name: 'Applied', count: 9, color: 'text-orange-400', borderColor: 'border-orange-700 hover:border-orange-500',
      description: 'Coherence bounds, entropy–drift relations, and threshold calibration. These connect the pure mathematics to the regime classification system.',
      keyLemmas: `
        <div class="space-y-1.5">
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2"><span class="font-mono text-orange-400 text-[10px]">L30</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-300">Entropy–drift bound: S is constrained by ω through CLT asymptotics</span></div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-2"><span class="font-mono text-orange-400 text-[10px]">L34</span> <span class="text-xs text-kernel-300">Drift threshold calibration via the heterogeneity gap</span></div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-kernel-600 mt-1">+ L26–L29, L31–L33 (coherence bounds, IC sensitivity, regime gate sharpness)</div>
        </div>`
    },
